From 89a7ed9c6dc205018fa2ac6d770d490ec60e4bae Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paul Cercueil <paul@crapouillou.net>
Date: Fri, 27 Aug 2021 17:39:56 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 0141/2399] drm/bridge: it66121: Wait for next bridge to be
 probed

If run before the next bridge is initialized, of_drm_find_bridge() will
give us a NULL pointer.

If that's the case, return -EPROBE_DEFER; we may have more luck next
time.

Signed-off-by: Paul Cercueil <paul@crapouillou.net>
Fixes: 988156dc2fc9 ("drm: bridge: add it66121 driver")
Reviewed-by: Neil Armstrong <narmstrong@baylibre.com>
Signed-off-by: Robert Foss <robert.foss@linaro.org>
Link: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/msgid/20210827163956.27517-2-paul@crapouillou.net
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/bridge/ite-it66121.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/bridge/ite-it66121.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/bridge/ite-it66121.c
index 06b59b422c69..d230fafea351 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/bridge/ite-it66121.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/bridge/ite-it66121.c
@@ -936,6 +936,9 @@ static int it66121_probe(struct i2c_client *client,
 		return -EPROBE_DEFER;
 	}
 
+	if (!ctx->next_bridge)
+		return -EPROBE_DEFER;
+
 	if (!ctx->next_bridge)
 		return -EPROBE_DEFER;
 
